CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 23, 1955, pg. 1, reads: "Crash Kills One - A two-car collision at Frankstown and Lang Avenues early Saturday morning, killed 17-year-old Harold Scott of 7373 Lemington Avenue, Penn Township, and seriously injured Norman R. Allen, 20, right, inset, of 1 East Lemington Avenue, also of Penn Township, and Thomas H. Croom, 27, left inset, of 2600 Wylie Avenue. The latter two were drivers of the cars which crashed into a confectionary store... and lower photo, Croom's car after the crash.  Both cars were completely wrecked, police said. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Wrecked 1955 Oldsmobile car driven by Thomas H. Croom with crumpled front end, parked in lot with warehouse or mill building in background
